    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Lime prepared by calcining limestone in a kiln at about 500 C to form a white amorphous powder that may contain small amounts of silica, iron, magnesium, and/or aluminum oxides. Oyster shells have been used to make a very pure quicklime. Once water is added, quicklime becomes slaked lime.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
